Slopes of \emph{p(x) = 0} at $x=0$, $x=2$ implies $p'(0)=p'(2)=0$

\begin{align*}\displaystyle p'(x)=3a_1x^2+2a_2x+a_3\end{align*}

When $\displaystyle p'(0)=0,$ $\displaystyle {}3a_{1}(0)^2+2a_2(0)+a_3=0$

When $\displaystyle p'(2)=0,$
$\displaystyle 3a_1(2)^2+2a_2(2)+a_3=0\rightarrow 12a_1+4a_2+a_3=0$

Hence, matrix \emph{A} is

\begin{align*}A=\begin{bmatrix}
12&4&1&0 \\ 
0& 0&1&0
\end{bmatrix}\end{align*}
